errorNotPlayer: [prefix] You must be a player to use the [commandName] command!
errorNoSubcommandProvided:
[prefix] You must specify which subcommand you want to use!

For help, try: /nation help
errorBadSubcommand:
[prefix] I could not find that subcommand!
For help, try: /nation help
errorCanNotRunOnYourself: [prefix] You can not run this command on yourself.
errorNationBadPermissions: [prefix] You must be at least a [minimumRole] to execute that command.
errorNationNotInNation: [prefix] You must be in a nation to execute that command.
errorNationNoPlayerFound: [prefix] No user found with the name [playerName]!
errorNationCreateNoNameProvided:
[prefix] You must provide a name for your nation.
Format: /nation create [name]
Example: /nation create My Cool Nation
errorNationCreateAlreadyInNation: [prefix] You must leave your current nation before creating a new one!
nationInviteInvited: [prefix] You have been invited to join [nationName] by [inviterName]!
errorNationInviteBadUsername:
[prefix] Bad username provided.
To invite a user to your nation please specify their name!
Format: /nation invite [username]
Example: /nation invite connor7000
errorNationJoinManual: [prefix] This is an automated command, ask someone to invite you, then click on the accept button.
errorNationJoinExpired: [prefix] This invitation has expired; ask for a new one!
errorNationJoinAlreadyInNation: [prefix] You are already in a nation.
errorNationLeaveIsChancellor:
[prefix] You may not leave a nation which you are the chancellor of.
You may either appoint a new chancellor with: /nation appoint [name].
Or you may disband your nation with: /nation disband
errorNationPromoteBadUsername:
[prefix] Bad username provided.
To promote a user please specify their name!
Format: /nation promote [username]
Example: /nation promote connor7000
errorNationDemoteBadUsername:
[prefix] Bad username provided.
To demote a user please specify their name!
Format: /nation demote [username]
Example: /nation demote connor7000
errorNationKickBadUsername:
[prefix] Bad username provided.
To kick a user please specify their name!
Format: /nation kick [username]
Example: /nation kick connor7000
errorNationAppointBadUsername:
[prefix] Bad username provided.
To appoint a user please specify their name!
Format: /nation appoint [username]
Example: /nation appoint connor7000
nationPower:
&nYour Nation Power&r: [nationPower]/[maxNationPower]
Member: [memberPower]/[maxMemberPower]
Rift: [riftPower]/[maxRiftPower]
&nYour Power&r: [playerPower]/[maxPlayerPower]
Passive: [playerPassivePower]/[maxPlayerPassivePower]
Bonus: [playerBonusPower]/[maxPlayerBonusPower]
nationPassivePowerIncremented:
[prefix] Your passive power just got increased to [passivePower]/[maxPassivePower]!
Your overall power is now [totalPower]/[maxTotalPower].
nationBonusPowerGained:
[prefix] You gained 1 bonus power for killing [killedName]!
You now have [bonusPower]/[bonusPowerMax] bonus power.
nationBonusPowerLowerLevel: [prefix] You did not gain any bonus power as [killedName] was a lower level than you.
nationBonusPowerMaxLevel: [prefix] You did not gain any bonus power for killing [killedName] as you are already at [bonusPower]/[bonusPowerMax].
nationPowerLost: [prefix] You lost [bonusPowerLost] bonus power and [passivePowerLost] passive power.
nationStatus:
&nNation Power&r: [nationPower]
Nation Claim Threshold: [nationClaimThreshold]
Nation Existence Threshold: [nationExistenceThreshold]
Chunks: [nationChunkCount]/[nationChunkMax]
Outposts: [nationOutpostCount]/[nationOutpostMax]
Protection: [status][nationProtectionDuration]&r
Auto reclaim protection: [statusChunk][nationChunkProtectionDuration]
blockHomeLore:
Where you place this block
will become your nation's home.
blockOutpostLore:
Where you place this block
will become one of your
nation's outposts.
giveBlock:
[prefix] You have been given a [blockName]&r!
Where you place this block will become your nation's home/outpost.
If you lose this block, you can get another with /nation claim [home] [outpost]
errorGiveBlockInventoryFull:
[prefix] Your inventory is full, so you did not get a [blockName]&r.
You can claim another with /nation claim [home] [outpost]
errorGiveBlockAlreadyOwned: [prefix] You already have a [blockName] in your inventory.
removeBlock:
[prefix] Removed your [blockName].
You can claim another with /nation claim [home] [outpost]
errorNationClaimHomeClaimed: [prefix] You have already claimed your home.
errorNationClaimReclaimPunishment: [prefix] You must wait [duration] before being able to claim again as an auto-reclaim punishment.
chunkClaimRift:
[prefix] Claimed [riftChunks] rift chunks adding [riftPower] power!
Now using [chunksClaimed]/[chunksClaimable] claims.
chunkClaimAutoEnabled: [prefix] Enabled automatic claiming, all chunks you enter will now be automatically claimed.
errorChunkClaimAutoNotInClaim: [prefix] You must be in one of your claims to enable automatic claiming.
errorChunkClaimAlreadyOwned: [prefix] This chunk is being defended by [defendingNationName] and is not currently overclaimable.
errorChunkClaimAlreadyOwnedByYou: [prefix] Your nation already owns this chunk.
errorChunkClaimAlreadyOwnedClaim: [prefix] This chunk is a home/outpost chunk being defended by [defendingNationName] and is not currently overclaimable.
errorChunkClaimNoNeighbour: [prefix] This chunk is not connected to any of your existing claims.
errorChunkClaimNoClaimsRift:
[prefix] Claiming this rift would require [riftChunks] claims.
You are already using [chunksClaimed]/[chunksClaimable] claims.
errorChunkUnclaimHome: [prefix] You can not unclaim your home chunk.
errorChunkUnclaimNotClaimed: [prefix] Your nation doesn't own this chunk.
errorChunkUnclaimMultipleUnclaimed:
[prefix] Unclaiming this chunk would unclaim [chunkCount] chunks.
To continue, use: /nation unclaim force
blockProtectedClaim: [prefix] You can not break claim blocks.
errorClaimSpecialOnRift: [prefix] You may not claim home/outpost on a rift.
claimOutpost:
[prefix] Claimed outpost [outpostNumber]!
You have now claimed [outpostsClaimed]/[outpostsCap] outposts.
errorClaimOutpostNoHome: [prefix] You must claim a home first.
overclaimStart:
[prefix] Started overclaiming one of [defendingNationName]'s chunks.
Stay in this chunk for [duration] without taking damage.
overclaimSuccessBroadcast:
[prefix] [attackingNationName] has overclaimed one of [defendingNationName]'s chunks!
[defendingNationName] lost [chunkCount] chunks.
overclaimFailMoved: [prefix] Overclaim failed, you can not move out of the chunk.
overclaimFailDamaged: [prefix] Overclaim failed, you can not take damage.
resupplySpawned:
[prefix] Spawned resupply minecart for outpost [outpostNumber].
You have [duration] to transport it to outpost [outpostNumber].
resupplyRespawn:
[prefix] Resupply minecart for outpost [outpostNumber] lost!
You have [duration] to transport the new one!
resupplyReminder: [prefix] Reminder: you have [duration] to resupply outpost [outpostNumber].
resupplyFail:
[prefix] Failed to resupply outpost [outpostNumber].
[chunkCount] chunks lost.
nationLockout:
[prefix] [nationName] has entered lockout!
View /nation status for more information.
nationLockoutExit: [prefix] [nationName] has exited lockout and is now safe!
nationLockoutReminder:
[prefix] Reminder: [nationName] is in lockout.
View /nation status for more information.
nationLockoutChunk:
[prefix] Your member count is too low to support your current land claims.
View /nation status for more information.
nationLockoutChunkReminder:
[prefix] Reminder: you have too many chunks claimed for your member count.
View /nation status for more information.
nationReclaimedChunks:
[prefix] [outpostCount] outposts and [chunkCount] chunks were automatically reclaimed.
You must now wait [claimPunishmentDuration] before claiming again.
nationHelp: [prefix] For help with Nations, check out our guide at &n[link]
errorNationMessageNoField: [prefix] You must specify which message you would like to update.
errorNationListBadPage: [prefix] That is not a valid page number.
pagePreviousTooltip: Click to go to the previous page.
pagePreviousNoneTooltip: You are already on the first page.
pageNextTooltip: Click to go to the next page.
pageNextNoneTooltip: You are already on the last page.
